## 5. Using the binding (example)

```ocaml
(* test.ml ----------------------------------------------------------- *)
let () =
  let rdr = Pcapng.open_file "sample.pcapng" in
  Printf.printf "Iterating over frames...\n";
  Pcapng.iter (fun f ->
      Printf.printf "ts=%Ld len=%d data[0]=0x%02X\n"
        f.Pcapng.timestamp f.Pcapng.captured_len
        (if f.Pcapng.captured_len > 0 then Char.code (Bytes.get f.Pcapng.data 0) else 0)
    ) rdr;
  Pcapng.close rdr
```

Compile with the library built above and you have a fully functional OCaml
binding that lets user‑code run *inside* the C++ iterator.

